cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the vulnerabilities of heterogeneous wireless networks (HWNs) to cyber risks and proposes a cyber insurance framework to address the problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the integration of cyber insurance as a service of next-generation HWNs, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
